---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Terms of Service | Epic Itineraries"
  description="Terms of service for Epic Itineraries â€” the rules and guidelines for using our platform."
>
  <Header transparent={false} />
  <main class="flex-1 pt-24">
    <div class="container max-w-3xl py-12">
      <h1 class="font-serif text-4xl font-normal italic text-primary mb-8">
        Terms of service
      </h1>

      <div class="max-w-none">
        <p class="text-lg text-muted-foreground mb-8">
          Last updated: February 2026
        </p>

        <section class="mb-8">
          <p class="text-muted-foreground">
            Epic Itineraries is a travel research platform that helps you save, organise, and
            turn web content into itineraries. By using it, you agree to these terms. If you
            don&rsquo;t agree, that&rsquo;s fine &mdash; but please don&rsquo;t use the service.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="mb-8">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4">Your account</h2>
          <p class="text-muted-foreground">
            You need an account to use Epic Itineraries. Keep your login details secure &mdash;
            you&rsquo;re responsible for what happens under your account. Use accurate
            information when signing up. You must be at least 16 years old.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="mb-8">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4">Your content</h2>
          <p class="text-muted-foreground">
            Everything you save, write, or create in Epic Itineraries belongs to you. We
            don&rsquo;t claim ownership of your collections, notes, or itineraries. We only
            store and display your content to provide the service. You can export or delete
            your data at any time.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="mb-8">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4">Acceptable use</h2>
          <p class="text-muted-foreground mb-4">
            Use Epic Itineraries for what it&rsquo;s built for: saving and organising travel
            research. Don&rsquo;t use it to:
          </p>
          <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-muted-foreground">
            <li>Break any laws</li>
            <li>Upload harmful or malicious content</li>
            <li>Try to compromise our systems or other users&rsquo; accounts</li>
            <li>Scrape or bulk-download content from the platform</li>
          </ul>
          <p class="text-muted-foreground mt-4">
            We can suspend or close accounts that violate these rules.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="mb-8">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4">AI features</h2>
          <p class="text-muted-foreground">
            Our AI itinerary generation is optional. When you use it, your collection data is
            sent to a third-party AI provider (Google Gemini) to create your itinerary. The AI
            works with what you&rsquo;ve saved &mdash; it doesn&rsquo;t invent destinations.
            See our <a href="/privacy" class="text-primary hover:underline">privacy policy</a>
            for details on how your data is handled.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="mb-8">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4">Service availability</h2>
          <p class="text-muted-foreground">
            We do our best to keep Epic Itineraries running smoothly, but we can&rsquo;t
            guarantee 100% uptime. The service is provided &ldquo;as is&rdquo;. We&rsquo;re
            not liable for any losses from downtime or bugs &mdash; though we&rsquo;ll
            always work to fix issues quickly.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="mb-8">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4">Termination</h2>
          <p class="text-muted-foreground">
            You can delete your account whenever you want. We may also close accounts that
            violate these terms. When an account is deleted, your data follows the process
            described in our <a href="/privacy" class="text-primary hover:underline">privacy
            policy</a> (soft-delete, then permanent removal after 30 days).
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="mb-8">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4">Changes</h2>
          <p class="text-muted-foreground">
            We may update these terms occasionally. If we make significant changes,
            we&rsquo;ll let you know. Continued use after changes means you accept them.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="mb-8">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4">Questions?</h2>
          <p class="text-muted-foreground">
            Reach us at
            <a
              href="mailto:hello@epic-itineraries.com"
              class="text-primary hover:underline"
            >
              hello@epic-itineraries.com
            </a>
          </p>
        </section>
      </div>
    </div>
  </main>
  <Footer />
</BaseLayout>
